# ftrack-sync

Scripts to sync development work with an ftrack instance.

## Installation

```sh
bun install
```

## Usage

Syncing GitHub PR status with task:

```sh
FTRACK_API_KEY="" FTRACK_URL="" FTRACK_LOGIN_EMAIL="" FTRACK_USER_ID="" PR_JSON="" GITHUB_TOKEN="" FTRACK_USER_ID="" bun run sync-pr-status
```

Checking that tasks have all necessary data:

```sh
FTRACK_API_KEY="" FTRACK_URL="" FTRACK_LOGIN_EMAIL="" FTRACK_USER_ID="" PR_JSON="" GITHUB_TOKEN="" FTRACK_USER_ID="" bun run check-tasks
```

Syncing release notes:

```sh
FTRACK_API_KEY="" FTRACK_URL="" FTRACK_LOGIN_EMAIL="" FTRACK_USER_ID="" ZENDESK_API_KEY="" ZENDESK_USERNAME="" RELEASE_JSON="" GITHUB_TOKEN="" bun run release-notes
```

## Tests

Run tests with `bun run test`.

During development of unit tests, it's helpful to enable watch mode with `bun run vitest`.
